Package: js2graphic
Title: Saving JavaScript Generated Plots As Graphics File
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Christoph", "Schmidt", email = "schmidtchristoph@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre","cph"))
Description: Some plotting packages produce figures generated by JavaScript code that open in
    web browsers or the RStudio Viewer pane. This package enables saving (most) of these figures in image file formats like .jpg or .png.
SystemRequirements:
    PhantomJS      (>= 2.1.1) (http://phantomjs.org),
    pdfcrop        (>= 1.38) (which is often shipped with LaTeX),
    ImageMagick    (>= 7.0.7-22) (http://www.imagemagick.org/),
    Ghostscript    (>= 9.21) (https://www.ghostscript.com)
Depends: R (>= 3.4.3)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    htmlwidgets    (>= 1.0),
    stringr        (>= 1.2.0)
Suggests:
    testthat       (>= 1.0.2),
    devtools       (>= 1.12.0),
    knitr          (>= 1.18),
    d3heatmap      (>= 0.6.1.1),
    networkD3      (>= 0.4),
    plotly         (>= 4.7.1),
    rsvg           (>= 1.1)
URL: https://github.com/schmidtchristoph/JS2Graphic
BugReports: https://github.com/schmidtchristoph/JS2Graphic/issues
ByteCompile: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
